== About ==
  The Rutgers CS352 Example Chat Client is a simple, peer-to-peer chat client
  that demonstrates basic network application practices.  It was designed in
  the summer of 2011 by Robert Moore and the students of the "Internet
  Technology" course at Rutgers University.  This version is maintained by
  Robert Moore and is distributed freely as an open-source project.

